result.execSummary:
The defendant Jimmy A. Clark was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jimmy A. Clark in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that an offer has been provided to the defendant and states plea agreement.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant asks that the surcharge be waived as he has paid that already twice.  Court notes that the surcharge cannot be waived.  Defendant wants to proceed with the offer.    Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant waives their right to an attorney.    Court finds waiver of Attorney made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Defendant enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  

BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty.

Atty Hendee asks the court to follow the recommendation.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.
